description:
Commit: 1b42443
Database: http://linked.opendata.cz/dump/dberr.zip
In the database, we have a triple
<http://linked.opendata.cz/resource/sukl/medicinal-product-packaging/0132829> dcterms:title "AMOKSIKLAV 1,2 G"@cs .

Using the SPARQL endpoint,
This works and returns that triple:
PREFIX r: <http://linked.opendata.cz/resource/sukl/medicinal-product-packaging/0132829>

CONSTRUCT {
  r: r: ?t .
}
 WHERE {
  OPTIONAL {
    r: dcterms:title ?t .
  }
  OPTIONAL {
    r: skos:prefLabel ?l .
  }
}

This does not work - returns an empty turtle, should have returned the same as above:
PREFIX r: <http://linked.opendata.cz/resource/sukl/medicinal-product-packaging/0132829>

CONSTRUCT {
  r: r: ?t , ?l .
}
 WHERE {
  OPTIONAL {
    r: dcterms:title ?t .
  }
  OPTIONAL {
    r: skos:prefLabel ?l .
  }
}

However, changing CONSTRUCT to SELECT works again (returns ?t and ?l is null):
PREFIX r: <http://linked.opendata.cz/resource/sukl/medicinal-product-packaging/0132829>

SELECT ?t ?l
 WHERE {
  OPTIONAL {
    r: dcterms:title ?t .
  }
  OPTIONAL {
    r: skos:prefLabel ?l .
  }
}

